(1, 'Michele Wie wins for first time in three years:', '2014-04-20', '16:44:00', 'Michele Wie claims her third win on tour after a three year absence from the winners circle:', 'Michelle Wie claimed her third LPGA Tour title and her first in over three and a half years with victory in the Lotte Championship.\r\n\r\nA five-under-par 67 in the final round at the Ko Olina Golf Club in Kapolei, Hawaii helped the American finish two shots ahead of her compatriot Angela Stanford, who carded a disappointing 73, and three clear of the world No1 Inbee Park.\r\n\r\nIt was 24-year-old Wie''s first title since winning the CN Canadian Women''s Open in August 2010, with her only other success coming in the Lorena Ochoa Invitational in November 2009.\r\n\r\nMuch was expected of Wie when she finished ninth on her major debut when only 13, and then almost made the halfway cut when competing against men at the Sony Open in her native Hawaii.\r\n\r\nShe was criticised, however, for continuing to accept PGA Tour invites as she struggled more and more. Injuries played their part too although there have been signs of an upturn in fortune this year with three top-10 finishes, including runner-up at the Kraft Nabisco Championship.'),
